    "He joined the navy in 1918 to serve in World War I where he was assigned as a radio electrician.": [],
    "After discharge in 1919 he was made associate editor of <em>The Dial</em>, a modernist literary magazine, continuing courses at the New School for Social Research where the social economist Thorstein Veblen (1857-1929) impressed him.": [],
    "Mumford married Sophia Wittenberg, whom he had met at the <em>Dial</em>, in 1921.": [],
    "By 1924, his first book on architecture, <em>Sticks and Stones</em>, and one of the first histories of American architecture, appeared.": [],
    "Critical of the beaux-arts tradition in architecture, the book argued for an indigenous American style.": [],
